Team roster for the daily PR digest cron (sent as Slack DM).

**<Group 1 name, e.g. "Engineering">:**

| Name | Email | GitHub handle |
|---|---|---|
| <Full Name> | <email@example.com> | `<handle>` |
| <Full Name> | <email@example.com> | `<handle>` |

**<Group 2 name, e.g. "Analytics">:**

| Name | Email | GitHub handle |
|---|---|---|
| <Full Name> | <email@example.com> | `<handle>` |

**<Group 3 name, e.g. "Design / Research">:**

| Name | Email | GitHub handle |
|---|---|---|
| <Full Name> | <email@example.com> | `<handle>` |

To re-discover a handle that stops returning results: search `org:<YOUR_GITHUB_ORG> is:pr "<Full Name>"` and match by author display name.

---

## Setup notes

Claude will populate the handle column on first run by:
1. Querying the employee directory (e.g. Glean's `employee_search`) for a GitHub profile link.
2. If empty, searching GitHub PRs authored by that person's full name and matching.
3. If still no luck, inspecting recent commits or branch names in your org.

Save this file to `~/.claude/projects/<your-sanitized-cwd>/memory/team_github_handles.md` (Claude knows where). After initial discovery, future runs skip the lookup.
